<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-11-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-11-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="147" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d147">
                    <head>No. 147.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Morton</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-11-13"><hi rend="italic">November</hi> 13,
                            1883</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 379.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose for your information a copy of Mr.
                        Schuyler’s dispatch, dated the 19th ultimo, and its accompaniment,
                        respecting the prohibition <pb facs="0362" n="292" xml:id="pg_292"/> by the
                        Hellenic Government of pork products coming from America, adding, what will
                        be particularly noted by you, that Greece otters, no reason for this action
                        save the precedent established by France.</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>